}}'''''Spy Snatcher''''' is a floppy disk-based text adventure released by [[Topologika]] Software in [[1988 in video gaming|1988]]. It was the last professional text adventure to be released on the [[BBC Micro]] and [[Acorn Electron]].{{Citation needed|date=October 2020}} It was also released for [[ZX Spectrum]] ([[ZX Spectrum#ZX Spectrum +3|+3]] disk only), [[RISC OS]], [[IBM PC compatible|PC]], [[Amstrad CPC]], [[Amstrad PCW]], [[Atari ST]] and [[RM plc|Nimbus]].[http://www.lysator.liu.se/adventure/Topologika_Ltd.html]

==Plot==
The secret plans for the Sonic Macrothrodule have been leaked to foreign powers by a mole.
You play an agent of MI7 and have only an hour to solve the puzzle and reveal the mole.

